<taxonomicName box="[151,409,1122,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Limassolla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutila" subGenus="L.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,283,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Limassolla</emphasis>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[300,325,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[342,409,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">rutila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Song &amp; Li sp. nov.
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,645,1122,1181]" box="[151,302,1157,1181]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,294,1157,1181]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Figs. 
<number box="[223,294,1157,1181]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="32.5" valueMax="37.0" valueMin="28.0">28–37</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1229,2010]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Crown (
<figureCitation box="[243,325,1229,1253]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[296,325,1229,1253]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
) brown yellow, with milky yellow symmetrical stripes at coronal suture and anterior margin. Eyes (
<figureCitation box="[159,240,1265,1289]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[211,240,1265,1289]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
) blackish brown. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[565,646,1265,1289]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[617,646,1265,1289]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
) milky yellow, with two black spots near anterior margin and posterior margin respectively; remaining patterns brown yellow, some parts with golden tint. Scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[1217,1299,1301,1325]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[1270,1299,1301,1325]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
) brown yellow; basal triangles grey, but median area dark, about triangular. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1024,1107,1337,1361]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[1078,1107,1337,1361]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
) narrow, with brown or nutbrown spots or stripes at apex; large orange red pattern around claval suture marked with short oblique dashes as in 
<figureCitation box="[151,230,1409,1433]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[202,230,1409,1433]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
and with other black markings near brochosome field.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1229,2010]" box="[197,1335,1445,1470]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Abdominal apodemes (
<figureCitation box="[457,538,1445,1469]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[509,538,1445,1469]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
) strong, well developed, extending to posterior margin of 
<number box="[1191,1204,1445,1469]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="5.0">5</number>
th segment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1229,2010]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[197,362,1481,1505]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer ventral appendage long and slender (
<figureCitation box="[897,983,1481,1505]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[951,983,1481,1505]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pygofer lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1167,1250,1481,1505]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[1221,1250,1481,1505]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
) with numerous microtrichia and microsetae scattered on lateral surface. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[993,1076,1517,1541]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[1047,1076,1517,1541]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
) slender, with single long macrosetae subbasally. Style (
<figureCitation box="[445,528,1553,1577]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[499,528,1553,1577]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
) with few fine setae on caudal part. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1077,1215,1553,1577]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Figs. 
<number box="[1142,1215,1553,1577]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="35.36">35, 36</number>
</figureCitation>
) with paired apical processes nearly triangular; preatrium distinctly longer than dorsal apodeme; gonopore preapical on posterior surface. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[354,436,1625,1649]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 37" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[164,1434,197,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,179,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 37. Limassolla rutila sp. nov. 28. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 29. Fore wing. 30. Hindwing. 31. Abdominal apodemes. 32. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 33. Subgenital plate. 34. Style. 35. Aedeagus, lateral view. 36. Aedeagus ventral view. 37. Connective, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[407,436,1625,1649]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
) Y-shaped, stem weakly bifid.
</paragraph>
